<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-59-0721 </DOCNO><TEXT>This paper describes the mechanisms of optoacoustic and optogalvanic effectsand shows how they can be succesfully applied to many different problemsin laser spectroscopy and related topics. Such unconventional detectiontechniques are also discussed from the point of view of their advantagesand limitations with respect to other techniques (C.P.).</TEXT></DOC>